After Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, where everything works better than with us, we were just in Russia witnessing that everything is still in its beginnings in the East.
In contrast to Prague, Moscow is not for people with disabilities, and it is still unusual for someone in a wheelchair to be alone in the city centre.
It is not even self-evident that a wheelchair user is given a lecture, for example, in the elevator.
